The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Chennai, Oct. 12 (PTI): More than 1,000 people face a ban of up to 10 years on travelling to Britain after their visa applications were rejected by the UK Border Agency (UKBA) in Chennai for allegedly containing forged documents or providing false information, a press release from British Deputy High Commission said today.          
	The release, quoting UKBA entry clearance manager Gemma Dodgson said their document checks were thorough and applications with false documents were turned down.                   
	 Chandigarh: Punjab and Haryana High Court has commuted the death sentence of Babbar Khalsa terrorist Jagtar Singh Hawara to life imprisonment in the Beant Singh assassination case. Beant Singh was the chief minister of Punjab in 1995.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): The income tax department has moved Bombay High Court to claim Rs 4 crore from actor Salman Khan in a tax evasion case for the assessment year 2000-2001. It has challenged an order of the appellate body which exempted him from paying the amount.                  
	 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): A nurse was murdered by some identified persons when she was returning home with her husband in a car near a village in Muzaffarnagar on Monday. Pammi, who worked at a hospital in Delhi, was strangled to death, police said.                   
	 Jammu (PTI): Ten persons, including four officials, have been arrested in connection with two ration scams in Jammu and Kashmirs Kishtwar and Rajouri district, sources said on Tuesday. The four officials allegedly misappropriated food grain worth over Rs 31 lakh, police said.
                                                                                                                                              
